  "text": "The LibreOffice document model architecture is built around a framework hierarchy of base classes. Here are the key files and classes:\n\n1. **SfxObjectShell** (include/sfx2/objsh.hxx, line 182) - This is the foundational base class for all document types in LibreOffice. It derives from SfxShell and SotObject, and implements the IEmbeddedHelper interface. All document shells inherit from this class to get core document functionality.\n\n2. **SfxApplication** (include/sfx2/app.hxx, line 103) - This is the LibreOffice application framework entry point and singleton. It manages the overall application state, document management, UI coordination, and serves as the command dispatcher for the entire application.\n\n3. **SwDoc** (sw/inc/doc.hxx, line 196) - This is the Writer (word processor) document class. It is marked as 'final' and contains all the core document model for text documents including paragraph styles, sections, frames, tables, and other text-specific content.\n\n4. **ScDocument** (sc/inc/document.hxx, line 331) - This is the Calc (spreadsheet) document class. It manages the spreadsheet model including sheets, cells, formulas, formatting, and calculation engine.\n\n5. **SdDrawDocument** (sd/inc/drawdoc.hxx, line 338) - This is the Impress/Draw document class, marked as 'final' and derived from FmFormModel. It manages the presentation model including slides, drawing objects, animations, and master pages.\n\nAll document types follow a similar pattern where the document class inherits from SfxObjectShell to integrate with LibreOffice's document framework. The SfxApplication manages instances of these document shells and coordinates their interaction through the framework."
}

